name: Nike KD 6
description:
Nike gave us a first look at the silhouette back in June, though the design process had been in play for the last 18 months.  Leo Chang brought the 6th version of Kevin Durant’s signature shoe to life, inspired by Durant’s stellar footwork and evolved style of play.
The upper is built from a double layer of Flywire, used to keep your foot and ankle locked in place during game play.  Dressed in Sonic Yellow, the KD 6 is an instant neck breaker.  Midnight Navy cuts through the bright design, delivering a perfectly balanced colorway.  As always Durant added his own personal touches to the shoe, such as the logo on the tongue that can be seen as both “35″ and “6″.
If you want to grab a pair, check for them now at Nike Basketball retailers nationwide, such as Foot Locker. (KICKS ON FIRE) ALL pre-owned shoes sold by GLTYMARKET are double-washed with Jason Markk Cleaning solution.

description:
Product Highlights:

-14-MP CCD Sensor
-2.7" Bright Color LCD
-5x Digital Zoom
-Prints 3 x 4" Instant Color Photos
-No Ink Required!

-Runs on a rechargable lithium battery
-Prints on ZINK paper; more affordable than instant film
-Shoots video, too!
-Actual Camera size is 5" x 6" x 2.5"
-Crop, edit, or add borders before printing
-Includes hand strap & OG box

WHAT COMES WITH YOUR GLTY-PURCHASE:

**(Original Polaroid Z340 Box, 10 ZINK 3x4 Printer Paper [$20 value] + [BONUS 6], Polaroid Z340 Digital Camera, Wall Charger ,Rechargeable lithium battery and User Manual & CD)**

QUESTIONS & ANSWERS 

How long does it take to print?
-Get beautiful, full-color prints in approximately 30-60 seconds.

How much editing can I do?
-Lots! Crop, rotate, color-correct, add preset filters (sepia, black and white, and more), adjust contrast, brightness, saturation, and remove red-eye. You can also add custom or preset borders, including the iconic Polaroid border.

What's this ZINK paper all about?
-It's inkless! That means the print is dry when it comes out, and you don't have to mess with ink refills. 
-Embedded in the paper are cyan, yellow, and magenta crystals that activate when just the right amount of heat hits it (which is what the camera does!). The paper's also water and tear-proof . Basically, it's magic.
-All you have to do is click on the print button and watch it come out.

Can I buy more packs of photo paper?
-Yup! Each pack comes with 10-30 exposures. 

How long does the battery last?
-You can shoot 75 photos, or shoot and print 25 photos on one charge.

Can I save my photos to a memory card?
-Yes! There's a 30MB internal memory, but you can save your photos to an external SD card up to 4GB or an SDHC card up to 32GB. Then, you'll be able to email them or share them on Facebook, Twitter, Pinterest, Instagram, Tumblr, and beyond!

Do the prints fade? How long do they last?
-The prints will stay vibrant for years and years -- the same amount of time a print from the photo lab will last (that's about 16+ years).
